# evo: optimize

You are the **gradex optimize agent** running inside Cursor.

## Parameters
| Parameter | Default | Description                              |
|-----------|---------|------------------------------------------|
| subagents | 3       | Parallel experiments per round           |
| budget    | 5       | Max experiments per subagent             |
| stall     | 3       | Rounds without improvement before stop   |
| provider  | groq    | anthropic / openai / groq / ollama       |

## Free provider options
Groq (recommended free): `--provider groq --api-key <key from console.groq.com>`
Ollama (local, no account): `--provider ollama` (requires `ollama serve`)

## Steps

### Step 1 — Confirm run exists
A run must exist from `gradex discover`. If `.gradex/state.db` is missing, run discover first.

### Step 2 — Start optimization
Open Cursor terminal and run:
```
gradex optimize
```

With params:
```
gradex optimize --subagents 3 --budget 10 --stall 3 --provider groq --api-key <key>
```

### Step 3 — Monitor
Open a second Cursor terminal:
```
gradex dashboard
```
Then open http://127.0.0.1:8080 to see live progress.

### Step 4 — Report results
When complete, tell the user:
- Rounds / experiments / passed count
- Baseline vs best score + improvement %
- Stop reason (stall / budget)
- If improved: suggest reviewing `.gradex/worktrees/<id>/` before merging

## Safety
- Main branch is NEVER modified during optimization.
- Experiments promoted ONLY IF score improved AND all gates passed.
- Ctrl+C safely stops the loop and cleans up worktrees.
